  "local_port": 40452,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you check an AT&T balance?",
  "response": "Checking your AT&T balance can be done through several methods, depending on whether you're a wireless, prepaid, or home services customer. Here\u2019s how you can check your balance:\n\n### **Wireless Customers:**\n1. **Online Account:**\n   - Log in to your AT&T account at [att.com](https://www.att.com).\n   - Navigate to the \"Usage\" or \"Billing\" section to view your balance and usage.\n\n2. **AT&T App:**\n   - Download the myAT&T app from the App Store or Google Play.\n   - Log in to your account and check your balance under the \"Usage\" or \"Billing\" section.\n\n3. **Text Message:**\n   - Dial *777# from your AT&T phone and follow the prompts to see your balance.\n\n4. **Customer Service:**\n   - Call AT&T customer service at 611 from your AT&T phone or **800-331-0500** from any phone.\n   - Follow the prompts to check your balance.\n\n### **Prepaid Customers:**\n1. **Online Account:**\n   - Visit the AT&T Prepaid account page at [paygonline.com](https://www.paygonline.com).\n   - Log in to view your balance and usage.\n\n2. **AT&T Prepaid App:**\n   - Download the myAT&T Prepaid app.\n   - Log in to check your balance.\n\n3. **Text Message:**\n   - Dial *777# from your AT&T phone to see your balance.\n\n4. **Customer Service:**\n   - Call AT&T Prepaid customer service at **800-901-9878**.\n\n### **Home Services Customers (Internet, TV, Phone):**\n1. **Online Account:**\n   - Log in to your account at [att.com](https://www.att.com).\n   - Go to the \"Billing\" section to view your balance.\n\n2. **Customer Service:**\n   - Call AT&T customer service at **800-288-2020** to check your balance.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\nAllowed content for the subject:\n- Make sure your account is up to date with the correct contact information to receive balance alerts.\n- Set up autopay to avoid missing payments and to keep track of your balance easily.\n\nIf you have any issues, AT&T\u2019s customer service team is available to assist you.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
